The paper deals with model checking algorithms for trees and graphs of bounded height, depth, and shrub-depth, which are all topics related to discrete structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves logical reasoning and complexity analysis, which suggests cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as another possible sub-category. The use of kernels and interpretation techniques indicates cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as potential sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
